## Summary Flow Diagram

```
User clicks "Continue Reading" on StoryDetail
    ↓
handleStartReading() extracts story.reading_progress.scroll_position
    ↓
navigate() with state: { scrollPosition: 0.35 }  (example 35% down)
    ↓
ChapterReader mounts → ReaderContent loads Lexical content
    ↓
contentReady = true triggers scroll restoration effect
    ↓
Double rAF waits for paint → window.scrollTo({ top: docHeight * 0.35 })
    ↓
navigate(pathname, { replace: true, state: {} })  // clears state
    ↓
User scrolls → scroll event fires every 3s (debounced)
    ↓
saveProgress() → saveReadingProgress() API call
    ↓
Backend upserts reading_progress table with chapter_id & scroll_position
    ↓
Next time: story.reading_progress fetched and cycle repeats
```

